│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                 │
│                                                                             │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                             │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                 │
│                                                                             │
│ The SLP vectorizer is crashing with an assertion failure in                 │
│ `isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry()` at line 12474. The assertion        │
│ expects that a gather node should have exactly one user                     │
│ (`TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.size() == 1`), but the debugger shows that         │
│ `TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.size()` is 0 for the problematic tree entry.        │
│                                                                             │
│ This tree entry (index 0) represents the bundle containing `%cmp4.3 = icmp  │
│ ne i32 %1, 0`, `%tobool10.not = icmp eq i32 %0, 0`, `%cmp4.2 = icmp ne i32  │
│ %2, %conv3.2`, and `%cmp4.1 = icmp ne i32 %2, %conv3.1`. It has state       │
│ `NeedToGather` and contains 4 scalars.                                      │
│                                                                             │
│ The issue occurs during horizontal reduction analysis when the vectorizer   │
│ tries to analyze gather nodes for potential shuffling. The code assumes     │
│ that all gather nodes in `ValueToGatherNodes` should have exactly one user, │
│ but this assumption is violated.                                            │
│                                                                             │
│ 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log:                                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ The debug log shows that the vectorizer successfully identifies and         │
│ schedules several bundles:                                                  │
│ - A bundle of compares (`%cmp4.2`, `%cmp4.1`)                               │
│ - A bundle of casts (`%conv3.2`, `%conv3.1`)                                │
│ - A bundle of xor operations (`%cmp2.2`, `%cmp2.1`)                         │
│                                                                             │
│ However, the initial bundle containing 4 icmp instructions (`%cmp4.3`,      │
│ `%tobool10.not`, `%cmp4.2`, `%cmp4.1`) fails to schedule: "We are not able  │
│ to schedule this bundle!"                                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ This unscheduled bundle becomes a gather node (state `NeedToGather`) with   │
│ no users in `UserTreeIndices`, which violates the assumption in             │
│ `isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry()`.                                    │
│                                                                             │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                     │
│                                                                             │
│ The root cause is that the assertion in                                     │
│ `isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry()` is too strict. When a gather node   │
│ cannot be scheduled (as in this case), it may legitimately have zero users  │
│ in `UserTreeIndices`. The code that populates `ValueToGatherNodes` includes │
│ such nodes, but the subsequent analysis assumes all gather nodes must have  │
│ exactly one user.                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ Looking at the context around line 12474, the function is trying to find    │
│ tree entries that share gathered values to determine if they represent a    │
│ shuffle permutation. However, it doesn't handle the case where a gather     │
│ node has no users, which can happen when the initial scheduling attempt     │
│ fails.                                                                      │
│                                                                             │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                  │
│                                                                             │
│ The assertion should be relaxed to allow gather nodes with zero users,      │
│ since this is a valid state for unscheduled gather nodes. The code should   │
│ handle this case gracefully by skipping such nodes rather than asserting.   │
│                                                                             │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                              │
│                                                                             │
│ The fix involves changing the assertion to allow `UserTreeIndices.size() == │
│ 0` in addition to the expected case of size 1. This handles the legitimate  │
│ scenario where a gather node cannot be scheduled and thus has no recorded   │
│ users. The surrounding code already has logic to handle empty `VToTEs`      │
│ collections, so allowing zero-user gather nodes should not break the        │
│ algorithm.                                                                  │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                             │
