12474. The assertion expects that a gather node should have exactly one user
(`TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.size() == 1`), but the debugger shows that
`TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.size()` is 0 for the problematic tree entry.\n\nThis
tree entry (index 0) represents the bundle containing `%cmp4.3 = icmp ne i32
%1, 0`, `%tobool10.not = icmp eq i32 %0, 0`, `%cmp4.2 = icmp ne i32 %2,
%conv3.2`, and `%cmp4.1 = icmp ne i32 %2, %conv3.1`. It has state
`NeedToGather` and contains 4 scalars.\n\nThe issue occurs during horizontal
reduction analysis when the vectorizer tries to analyze gather nodes for
potential shuffling. The code assumes that all gather nodes in
`ValueToGatherNodes` should have exactly one user, but this assumption is
violated.\n\n2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log:\n\nThe debug log shows that the
vectorizer successfully identifies and schedules several bundles:\n- A bundle
of compares (`%cmp4.2`, `%cmp4.1`)\n- A bundle of casts (`%conv3.2`,
`%conv3.1`)\n- A bundle of xor operations (`%cmp2.2`, `%cmp2.1`)\n\nHowever,
the initial bundle containing 4 icmp instructions (`%cmp4.3`, `%tobool10.not`,
`%cmp4.2`, `%cmp4.1`) fails to schedule: \"We are not able to schedule this
bundle!\"\n\nThis unscheduled bundle becomes a gather node (state
`NeedToGather`) with no users in `UserTreeIndices`, which violates the
assumption in `isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry()`.\n\n3. Root Cause
Analysis:\n\nThe root cause is that the assertion in
`isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry()` is too strict. When a gather node
cannot be scheduled (as in this case), it may legitimately have zero users in
`UserTreeIndices`. The code that populates `ValueToGatherNodes` includes such
nodes, but the subsequent analysis assumes all gather nodes must have exactly
one user.\n\nLooking at the context around line 12474, the function is trying
to find tree entries that share gathered values to determine if they represent
a shuffle permutation. However, it doesn't handle the case where a gather node
has no users, which can happen when the initial scheduling attempt fails.\n\n4.
Proposed Edit Point(s):\n\nThe assertion should be relaxed to allow gather
nodes with zero users, since this is a valid state for unscheduled gather
nodes. The code should handle this case gracefully by skipping such nodes
rather than asserting.\n\n5. Conclusion:\n\nThe fix involves changing the
assertion to allow `UserTreeIndices.size() == 0` in addition to the expected
case of size 1. This handles the legitimate scenario where a gather node cannot
be scheduled and thus has no recorded users. The surrounding code already has
logic to handle empty `VToTEs` collections, so allowing zero-user gather nodes
should not break the algorithm.",
  "test_traj": [
    "diff --git a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp
b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\nindex
1098bf578d2d..ef44da8fb611 100644\n---
a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\n+++
b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\n@@ -12471,8 +12471,8 @@
BoUpSLP::isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry(\n
assert(any_of(TEPtr->Scalars,\n                     [&](Value *V) { return
GatheredScalars.contains(V); }) &&\n              \"Must contain at least
single gathered value.\");\n-      assert(TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.size() == 1
&&\n-             \"Expected only single user of a gather node.\");\n+
assert((TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.size() == 1 || TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.empty())
&&\n+             \"Expected at most single user of a gather node.\");\n
const EdgeInfo &UseEI = TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.front();\n \n       PHINode
*UserPHI = dyn_cast<PHINode>(UseEI.UserTE->getMainOp());\n",
    "diff --git a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp
b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\nindex
1098bf578d2d..b65fbf4c5559 100644\n---
a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\n+++
b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\n@@ -12471,6 +12471,9 @@
BoUpSLP::isGatherShuffledSingleRegisterEntry(\n
assert(any_of(TEPtr->Scalars,\n                     [&](Value *V) { return
GatheredScalars.contains(V); }) &&\n              \"Must contain at least
single gathered value.\");\n+      // Skip gather nodes with no users as they
cannot contribute to shuffle analysis.\n+      if
(TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.empty())\n+        continue;\n
assert(TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.size() == 1 &&\n              \"Expected only
single user of a gather node.\");\n       const EdgeInfo &UseEI =
TEPtr->UserTreeIndices.front();\n"
  ]
